Inside, the pigs came up with a clever idea. They built a trap using sticks and straw from their demolished houses. When the wolf grew impatient and tried to force his way into Penny's house, Red Riding Hood led him to the trap. The wolf, unsuspecting, stepped on the weak spot, and the trap sprang, trapping him.

With the wolf caught, the four friends celebrated their victory. They freed the wolf only after he promised never to bother them or anyone else in the forest again. From that day on, the three little pigs and Little Red Riding Hood remained the best of friends, always looking out for one another in their enchanted forest home. [end of text]


